form_title.ms_form_title_llm_v1: Information Furnished On This Form Is CONFIDENTIAL Screened by NARA, 7/3/2023, 1975-211-073/7

full_text: Information Furnished On This Form Is by NARA, 7/3/2023 FOR DISTRICT OFFICE USE INSTRUCTIONS One Number Is All You Ever Need For Social Security And Tax Purposes Special Attention Should Be Given To Items Listed Below Fill in this form completely and correctly. If any information is not known and is unavailable, write "unknown" Use typewriter or print legibly in dark ink. I Your social security card will be typed with the name you show in item 1. However, if you want to use the name shown in item 2, attach o signed request to this form. 3 If not born in the USA, enter the name of the country in which you were born 5 If a stepfather, adopting father, or foster father is shown, include the relationship after name, for example, "John H. Jones, stepfather." If you have ever before filled out an application like this for o social security, rail- road, or tax number, check "yes" even if You never received your card. If you check "yes," give the name of the State and the approximate date on which you applied. Also enter your social security number if you did receive the card and re- member the number. You may find your number on on old tax return, payroll slip, or wage statement If you get your mail in the country, without 0 street address, show your R.D. Route, and Box number, if of the post office, show your P.O. Box No.: if there is no FOR BUREAU OF DATA PROCESSING such way of showing your mail address, show the town or post office name. If mail under your name is not normally received of the address which you show, use on "in care of" address. 14 Sign your name as usually written Do not print unless this is your usual signature. (If unable to write, make a mark witnessed by two persons who can write. The witnesses preferably should be persons who work with the applicant and both must sign this application. A parent, guardian, or custodian who completes this form on behalf of another person should sign his own name followed by his title or relation- ship to the applicant; for example, "John Smith, father.")
